<subSubSection id="6595B2290A3DCAACFF946902579FCFE2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9F112D176A00BDE5939CFFAFBD3C5BAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C04F907E12C7C28C0A0A9504C076902E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="02B39A9151E4A5AC53C5AD08719FD8BD" authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora xinglongensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis id="F3D109C786D91835073600359D50E68B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="2BC7E6A4E89A17C152F40C98C90EE2CE" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. californica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="californica">
<emphasis id="4F79D8B62EDF268ED11E429123AE8A6E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. californica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="71D421A9A25F523EE67CB08E2AA717F5" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. eucalypti" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="eucalypti">
<emphasis id="155E8E73FD3DF6DB8D52D44795202EF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. eucalypti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by longer conidia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9FF500DC0094BBCC34B22D3D19F06D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="377F6EF340B8E69B444A2513E143C2D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0895FE70496E96298261B4493D9E97CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Named after the county where it was collected, Xinglong County.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F16F28E78037476181BD73F17B543EBA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="57DB6DBB8A98B13E5781F85164CDEBC6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="795319FB29C9E520B93791518C0D6E20" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Sexual morph: not observed. Asexual morph: Pycnidial stromata immersed in bark, erumpent through the surface of bark, discoid, with a solitary undivided locule. Conceptacle black, circular surrounded stromata. Ostiole inconspicuous. Locules undivided, circular to ovoid, (480-)540-685(-755) 
<normalizedToken id="EF1D3C4BE77AA60F7270A05A0A3629B9" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam. Conidiophores hyaline, unbranched. Peridium comprising a few layers of cells of textura angularis, with innermost layer brown, outer layer brown to dark brown. Conidiogenous cells enteroblastic polyphialidic, (4.5-)6.5-8.5(-12) 
<normalizedToken id="4B7E01F33B14BD7260239B3CB9266933" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="6F715FB5FC6DB22D835DAFB5C73FB893" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(x̄ = 7.4 
<normalizedToken id="FEA3ACE56257BD5FE3C8726F778220F9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.3 
<normalizedToken id="E9E4764F63DAF2D910224DB0AEABA95B" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
). Conidia hyaline, allantoid, eguttulate, smooth, aseptate, thin-walled, (7.5-)8.5-9.5(-10.5) 
<normalizedToken id="C830BDE2C5F89B67CC168B5A2905DA46" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="F3BF89B3BCE0449B33DE900262A142E3" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(x̄ = 8.9 
<normalizedToken id="9117BD25CB81ED7799BFD59377DE3358" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.3 
<normalizedToken id="A468F85A54777AA903BFC943507497B6" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7191FFF517DDF396DB5313C4A71D23E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="CD3E401A1220709A4057FF25566D1184" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Culture characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="827226B9F54E5547EC8F62F4B0E91391" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">On PDA at 25 °C in darkness. Cultures are white. The colony is flat, thin with a uniform texture, lacking aerial mycelium. Pycnidia distributed uniformly on medium surface.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DF073B7C1063988C4C745432F5AE70E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="3B0EA0BADB24DB7BFE2798B90F970A5F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Specimens examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="03D2C9F30DA6B11D989B6B712B0A050F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
China, Hebei Province, Chengde City, Xinglong County, chestnut plantation, 
<geoCoordinate id="7D50B31396FE4F47C86529DCD7CF7161" degrees="40" direction="north" minutes="24" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="32" value="40.40889">40°24'32&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="4A32EA9061B2067AD29106B66F064953" degrees="117" direction="east" minutes="28" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="56" value="117.48222">117°28'56&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, on branches of 
<taxonomicName id="FA5F84A5C71CC4B5107E3776FAEE15FD" class="Thecofilosea" family="Castanellidae" genus="Castanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Castanea mollissima" order="Phaeocalpida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mollissima">
<emphasis id="95BCF38E0D165EC5BBE486186C8767C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Castanea mollissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 11 October 2017, N. Jiang (
<emphasis id="733DB8BAA8421E7C5183DF981BDB1B66" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">holotype</emphasis>
BJFC-S1706, ex-type living culture CFCC 52458; 
<emphasis id="0CEF9FEEE56061954118DA0E851DF682" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">paratype</emphasis>
BJFC-S1707, living culture CFCC 52459).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2483C1C552DD9D811C58533E6075393" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="85C7F5770ECAF5489E819BB423F069CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E041128B912217C65A125790F418EA1D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="17C96276DE12DE23C2F9380F3FB2179C" authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora xinglongensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis id="D97DF56384E0680EEF7A92D7581FF6EE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is associated with canker disease of 
<taxonomicName id="1121D250413310724DAC6BB48BFEDB9D" class="Thecofilosea" family="Castanellidae" genus="Castanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Castanea mollissima" order="Phaeocalpida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mollissima">
<emphasis id="D3C23C4E810CC871ABDB4CC9D653904F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Castanea mollissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in China. 
<taxonomicName id="DB63970D7EEBD74EF60AC0C579BA1AC4" authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora xinglongensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis id="2333A2CE6E159E801EFE1FB418CCBC8C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from its phylogenetically closely species 
<taxonomicName id="A39C5907D8C02162EE4064B6E195DEA0" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. thailandica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="thailandica">
<emphasis id="828BC10616D0349A7227EBCAE68F46E6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. thailandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having much longer conidia (8.5-9.5 
<normalizedToken id="DFB4E340DFB0883ADA51ADC3BB753E17" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="1010AAAB0179091EC1DED68DA552B366" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. xinglongensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis id="E193B0ED2DB2CE3E99CEC526D8CFD2FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 3.3-4 
<normalizedToken id="E285DAE07057C1E40AB307F5BEFAD9A3" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="627FEA8EBE29956A1A3990970FF5893F" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. thailandica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="thailandica">
<emphasis id="C9296F2665A5E581B7C14841EEDE46D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. thailandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="E83CB0DD5BD4656F3642B374031D01E9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.38.28011" author="Norphanphoun, C" journalOrPublisher="Mycokeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="93 - 120" refId="B31" refString="Norphanphoun, C, Raspe, O, Jeewon, R, Wen, TC, Hyde, KD, 2018. Morphological and phylogenetic characterisation of novel Cytospora species associated with mangroves. Mycokeys 38: 93 - 120, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.38.28011" title="Morphological and phylogenetic characterisation of novel Cytospora species associated with mangroves." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.38.28011" volume="38" year="2018">Norphanphoun et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="DFEDD26E7371D202E73714581B8E25CF" authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; N. Jiang" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora xinglongensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xinglongensis">
<emphasis id="E3653A8D784517465BCD172136F80291" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora xinglongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="A8EE469537B8A2502643257D650654AE" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. thailandica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="thailandica">
<emphasis id="163E0BE440B7A47E9CA0EC39DC7FAF46" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. thailandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by ITS, ACT and RPB2 loci (16/470 in ITS, 22/245 in ACT and 52/726 in RPB2).
</paragraph>
